{"bill":{"bill_id":1651342,"change_hash":"e0906ed21ff3e7ba338d447286067c01","session_id":1988,"session":{"session_id":1988,"state_id":46,"year_start":2023,"year_end":2023,"prefile":0,"sine_die":0,"prior":0,"special":0,"session_tag":"Regular Session","session_title":"2023 Regular Session","session_name":"2023 Regular Session"},"url":"https:\/\/legiscan.com\/VA\/bill\/SB1221\/2023","state_link":"https:\/\/lis.virginia.gov\/cgi-bin\/legp604.exe?231+sum+SB1221","completed":0,"status":2,"status_date":"2023-02-06","progress":[{"date":"2023-01-10","event":1},{"date":"2023-01-10","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-03","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-06","event":2},{"date":"2023-02-10","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-14","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-17","event":2},{"date":"2023-02-24","event":2},{"date":"2023-02-24","event":2}],"state":"VA","state_id":46,"bill_number":"SB1221","bill_type":"B","bill_type_id":"1","body":"S","body_id":8,"current_body":"H","current_body_id":7,"title":"Assisted living facilities; minimum liability insurance.","description":"Assisted living facilities; minimum liability insurance. Requires the Board of Social Services to adopt regulations requiring each assisted living facility to maintain a minimum amount of liability insurance, as determined by the Board, and provide notice of such insurance, upon request, to any resident or prospective resident. Under current law, assisted living facilities must provide a statement disclosing whether the facility maintains liability insurance but can only state that it does if it meets a minimum amount of coverage established by the Board. The bill provides that no assisted living facility shall be immune from civil liability on the grounds that it is a charitable institution for damages equal to or less than the greater of (i) the limits of the liability insurance coverage maintained by the assisted living facility or (ii) the minimum amount of liability insurance coverage that the assisted living facility is required to maintain by regulation. Assisted living facilities; minimum liability insurance. Requires the Board of Social Services to adopt regulations requiring each assisted living facility to maintain a minimum amount of liability insurance, as determined by the Board, and provide notice of such insurance, upon request, to any resident or prospective resident. Under current law, assisted living facilities must provide a statement disclosing whether the facility maintains liability insurance but can only state that it does if it meets a minimum amount of coverage established by the Board. The bill provides that no assisted living facility shall be immune from civil liability on the grounds that it is a charitable institution for damages equal to or less than the greater of (i) the limits of the liability insurance coverage maintained by the assisted living facility or (ii) the minimum amount of liability insurance coverage that the assisted living facility is required to maintain by regulation.","pending_committee_id":0,"committee":[],"referrals":[{"date":"2023-01-10","committee_id":168,"chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"name":"Rehabilitation and Social Services"},{"date":"2023-02-10","committee_id":154,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Health, Welfare and Institutions"}],"history":[{"date":"2023-01-10","action":"Prefiled and ordered printed; offered 01\/11\/23 23102141D","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-10","action":"Referred to Committee on Rehabilitation and Social Services","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-02-03","action":"Reported from Rehabilitation and Social Services with amendments (13-Y 0-N 1-A)","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-02-03","action":"Constitutional reading dispensed (38-Y 0-N)","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-02-06","action":"Printed as engrossed 23102141D-E","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-02-06","action":"Read second time",